> You need to be aware that most built-in string functions won't workActually the non-mb string functions will work perfectly fine for almost everything. For example splitting on space or comma, or joining strings will work just fine with UTF-8. The only things that don't work are those that split by character position. Even search works fine.> You need to set internal encoding to UTF-8 for some extensions in php.ini. ini_set('default_charset', 'UTF-8');
 mb_internal_encoding("UTF-8");

> You need to normalize all input yourselfOnly if you need to compare against it (for example to see if the username was taken). Most of the time you just store the input as is.For PCRE make sure to add the /u option.
